race.comment: A host of key scratchings rob this race of its original depth. MAYBE MOET (3) settled worse than midfield then lengthened nicely to miss a first-up win narrowly over this course and distance a fortnight ago. Goes up 5kgs but this is a significant class drop. Should be winning with J Mac up. ZOE (12) is in the mix dropping back in trip at the third run of the campaign. Raced handy but weakened at the end of 1400m at Warwick Farm last time. Coming back to this trip is the right move. The lightly raced MANAAJEM (7) is back after a 230-day spell. Turned in a nice trial at Rosehill recently. Has plenty of upside and should be in the finish. The consistent NYMPHADORA (8) is one for the exotics first-up from a spell. LADY YARROW (6) bolted in when fresh from a nine-week break at the Sapphire Coast recently. Will find this a lot harder but she is another worth including in trifectas and first fours.
